## Additional Use Grant Details

### Permitted Uses

You MAY use the Licensed Work for:

✅ **Internal business use** - Deploy and use Specular within your organization for your own development needs, regardless of organization size

✅ **Consulting and integration services** - Use Specular as part of professional services where you are not selling Specular itself as a service

✅ **Educational purposes** - Use Specular for teaching, research, or academic purposes

✅ **Personal projects** - Use Specular for your own personal or hobbyist projects

✅ **Open-source projects** - Use Specular for developing open-source software

✅ **Evaluation and testing** - Evaluate Specular for potential adoption

✅ **Modifications** - Create modified versions for allowed uses

### Prohibited Uses

You MAY NOT use the Licensed Work for:

❌ **Commercial SaaS offerings** - Provide Specular as a hosted service, managed service, or SaaS product to third parties for a fee

❌ **Competing services** - Offer any commercial service that competes with Specular's core business of AI-assisted specification and build services

❌ **Cloud provider managed services** - Package or resell Specular as a managed service on AWS, Azure, GCP, or other cloud platforms

❌ **Embedding in competing products** - Integrate Specular into a product that directly competes with Specular

### Examples

**✅ ALLOWED**:
- A Fortune 500 company uses Specular internally for all their development teams
- A consulting firm uses Specular to build client applications (but doesn't sell Specular itself)
- A university uses Specular to teach software engineering
- An individual developer uses Specular for personal projects
- A company modifies Specular for internal use

**❌ PROHIBITED**:
- A cloud provider offers "Managed Specular" as a service
- A company creates "Specular-as-a-Service" and charges users
- A platform embeds Specular and offers it as a competing AI development assistant
- A company builds a competing AI specification and build service using Specular's code

### Need a Commercial License?

If your use case is prohibited under this license, please contact us for commercial licensing options:
- Email: felix@felixgeelhaar.de
- Website: https://github.com/felixgeelhaar/specular

