## Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: Is this Open Source?**
A: No, the Business Source License is not an Open Source license. However, the code becomes Open Source (Apache 2.0) automatically after the Change Date (2 years).

**Q: Can I use Specular at my company?**
A: Yes! Internal business use is fully permitted, regardless of company size.

**Q: Can I contribute to Specular?**
A: Yes! Contributions are welcome. By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the same BSL terms.

**Q: Can I fork Specular?**
A: Yes, you can fork and modify Specular for permitted uses. However, you cannot use a fork to provide prohibited commercial services.

**Q: What happens after the Change Date?**
A: The Licensed Work automatically becomes available under Apache License 2.0, making it fully Open Source.

**Q: Can I sell services using Specular?**
A: Yes, if you're selling consulting or integration services. No, if you're selling Specular itself as a hosted service.

**Q: How is this different from AGPL?**
A: AGPL requires you to open-source modifications if you run the software as a service. BSL prohibits certain commercial uses entirely, but is more permissive for other uses (like internal business use).

